  "course_notes": "(Same as AAS 190 1) (Freshmen Seminar - Limited to First Year Students Only) (Complete Topic: Black Women and the Politics of Beauty) (Why is Beyonce often called beautiful and Lupita often called \"striking\"? This course examines how representations of the black female body are manipulated to reflect excess and chaos - unruly hair, too much flesh, too sexual, too dark - instead of expanding cultural concepts of beauty in mainstream American idealism.)",
